{"key":"post-8989842","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8989842</id>\n<content>Don't try to pour the dishes first.&amp;nbsp; They'll contaminate as they cool due to so many available points of entry.&amp;nbsp; Let it cool most of the way in the whiskey bottle with a filter on the lid.&amp;nbsp; Pour when you can handle the bottle without heat protection for your hands.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In addition, if you pour the petri dishes first, the agar tends to spill all over the place when you move the PC or unload the dishes. Good luck.&amp;nbsp; Don't forget to use a glovebox.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8989845</next>\n<prev>8989834</prev>\n<first>8982938</first>\n<last>8989845</last>\n<when>1222461589</when>\n<utime>09/26/08 11:39 PM</utime>\n</post>"}